On December 23, 2022, the President signed into law the "James M. Inhofe National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2023." This law authorizes appropriations for various programs including the Department of Defense, Department of Energy national security programs, and Intelligence programs. It also specifies a military basic pay increase and grants other authorities to the U.S. Armed Forces. Additionally, the law authorizes appropriations for the Department of State, Department of Homeland Security, Maritime Administration, U.S. Coast Guard, and the Intelligence Community. Senators Reed and Inhofe, Representatives Adam Smith and Mike Rogers, and others are acknowledged for their leadership in this matter.